{"id":2326,"category_slug":"medical-english-oet","category_name":"Medical English (OET)","position":58,"title":"Test 06 - Part B - Extract 6","subtitle":"Blood Pressure Medication Oversight","level":"B2","parts":16,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6.2326/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/0-test-06-part-b-extract-6.mp3","transcript":"Ah, nurse, hello.\nI'm wondering if you can help me.\nI've just been going over the charts for Mr Chew in bed 34\nand I'm wondering why I wasn't told that his blood pressure medications were being held over the past few days.\nHi Dr Griezman.\nRight, I'm not sure.\nI didn't even know that had happened.\nLet me look into it and I'll get back to you.\nThere's no need for that.\nI've been sitting here for 20 minutes looking at the blood pressures and medications that have been given to the patient\nand it simply doesn't make any sense.\nWell, I really don't know, Dr. Griezman.\nI've literally taken care of this patient for four hours.\nI can discuss it with the nursing director, though, if you like.\nNo, that isn't necessary.\nThank you, nurse.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:53:09","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Ah, nurse, hello.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/1.mp3","time_start":1.12,"time_end":2.95},{"position":2,"content":"I'm wondering if you can help me.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/2.mp3","time_start":2.95,"time_end":4.46},{"position":3,"content":"I've just been going over the charts for Mr Chew in bed 34","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/3.mp3","time_start":4.46,"time_end":7.93},{"position":4,"content":"and I'm wondering why I wasn't told that his blood pressure medications were being held over the past few days.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/4.mp3","time_start":7.93,"time_end":13.21},{"position":5,"content":"Hi Dr Griezman.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/5.mp3","time_start":13.21,"time_end":14.61},{"position":6,"content":"Right, I'm not sure.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/6.mp3","time_start":14.61,"time_end":16.99},{"position":7,"content":"I didn't even know that had happened.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/7.mp3","time_start":16.99,"time_end":19.01},{"position":8,"content":"Let me look into it and I'll get back to you.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/8.mp3","time_start":19.01,"time_end":21.1},{"position":9,"content":"There's no need for that.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/9.mp3","time_start":21.1,"time_end":22.52},{"position":10,"content":"I've been sitting here for 20 minutes looking at the blood pressures and medications that have been given to the patient","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/10.mp3","time_start":22.52,"time_end":27.67},{"position":11,"content":"and it simply doesn't make any sense.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/11.mp3","time_start":27.67,"time_end":29.99},{"position":12,"content":"Well, I really don't know, Dr. Griezman.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/12.mp3","time_start":29.99,"time_end":32.39},{"position":13,"content":"I've literally taken care of this patient for four hours.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/13.mp3","time_start":32.39,"time_end":35.55},{"position":14,"content":"I can discuss it with the nursing director, though, if you like.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/14.mp3","time_start":35.55,"time_end":38.56},{"position":15,"content":"No, that isn't necessary.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/15.mp3","time_start":38.56,"time_end":40.27},{"position":16,"content":"Thank you, nurse.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-06-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-22-17-14/16.mp3","time_start":40.27,"time_end":41.67}]}